docs/m015_failure_ledger.md:27:| `tests/action_affordance_consumers.rs`, `tests/action_affordance_query.rs`, `tests/boundary_contract.rs`, `tests/combat_coherence.rs`, `tests/damage_breakdown_log.rs`, `tests/encounter_e2e.rs`, `tests/engine_legality_integration.rs`, `tests/event_stream.rs`, `tests/patamon_revive.rs`, `tests/resource_caps.rs`, `tests/revive_semantics.rs`, `tests/sp_economy.rs`, `tests/status_effect_apply.rs`, `tests/status_effect_integration.rs`, `tests/toughness_categories.rs`, `tests/ultimate_meter.rs` | Mechanical stale fixture drift | Current `cargo test --no-run` output still reports `missing fields animation_sequence and qte in initializer of SkillDef` in the listed targets; the older S01 research inventory shows the full affected set. | S03 (fixture/schema refresh) |
docs/m015_failure_ledger.md:58:| `tests/twin_core_mechanics.rs`, `tests/validation_snapshot.rs` | Architecture-drift candidate, not a simple fixture fix | Current `src/combat/twin_core.rs` exposes `cross_resonance`, `active_thermal_spark_targets`, `fire_spend_markers`, `ice_spend_markers`, `twin_burst_used_this_cycle`, `shatter_used_this_cycle`, and `last_signal`; it does **not** expose `resonance` / `heat`. The stale tests are asserting an older contract. | S02/S03 (confirm current Twin Core model before rewriting tests) |
docs/combat_design_revised.md:1:Sì: il sistema è coerente e la direzione è appagante. La cosa da sistemare prima del vero “production lock” non è più il fantasy dei kit, ma la **precisione delle regole**: durata dei tag, trigger di Strain/Flow, anti-loop, conversione degli hard-control sui boss e livello roguelite tra un fight e l’altro.
docs/combat_design_revised.md:96:| **HEAVY-BREAKER**   | Alto Toughness Damage                       |
docs/combat_design_revised.md:254:| `Kofuda`               | Nemico       |           Fino alla prossima Skill nemica |               No | Consumato dal trigger            |
docs/combat_design_revised.md:290:| Toughness lock          | Non blocca phase reset                           |
docs/combat_design_revised.md:303:4. Toughness Damage;
docs/combat_design_revised.md:304:5. trigger Heavy;
docs/combat_design_revised.md:306:7. trigger follow-up/counter;
docs/combat_design_revised.md:402:**BREAK:** Heavy-Breaker, più Heat Sink = più Toughness Damage.
docs/combat_design_revised.md:473:* Con Spark: consuma Spark e applica `Deep Crack`, aumentando Toughness Damage ricevuto.
docs/combat_design_revised.md:913:Quando uno infligge Toughness Damage, l’altro contribuisce con il 50% del proprio prossimo Toughness Damage.
docs/combat_design_revised.md:919:Il target non rigenera Toughness per 1 Tactical Cycle.
docs/combat_design_revised.md:939:* +Toughness Damage;
docs/combat_design_revised.md:1086:Se target ha Toughness sotto 50%, resetta la barra Toughness.
docs/combat_design_revised.md:1165:* +1 Toughness Damage;
docs/combat_design_revised.md:1175:* massimo 1 trigger per Tactical Cycle;
docs/combat_design.md:17:Riduzione di scope per release iniziale: sistemi Mark/Assist Fire, Momentum, Phase Action, Stability (Window e Punitive), Anti-Evolved trait family, Tamer Commands secondari, Toughness varianti avanzate, Ultimate Windows multiple, Damage Tags ridondanti — tutti rimossi o tagliati a versione minima. Aggiunto schema DNA Chips e schema EvoStage forward-compat. Vedi changelog finale.
docs/combat_design.md:24:La battaglia si vince preparando il team giusto, scegliendo la forma giusta e leggendo Attribute, Damage Tag, Intent, Toughness e risorse.
docs/combat_design.md:41:* +15% Toughness damage
docs/combat_design.md:73:Include Basic Attack e Skill. Può generare SP (solo Basic), Energy piena, status, Break, e triggerare reazioni.
docs/combat_design.md:116:# 6. Toughness / Break / DoT
docs/combat_design.md:119:Toughness e Break esistono **solo lato nemico**. Gli alleati non hanno una barra Toughness.
docs/combat_design.md:121:## Categorie di Toughness Nemica (MVP: 3 sole)
docs/combat_design.md:122:* **Standard Toughness**: comportamento normale.
docs/combat_design.md:123:* **Armored Toughness**: alta Toughness, HP più basso. Tipico di Elite.
docs/combat_design.md:124:* **Shielded Toughness**: non può essere Broken finché una condizione non viene risolta (vedi Break Seal). Tipico di Boss.
docs/combat_design.md:134:DoT non possono causare Break, ma preparano il "Break Setup" a 1 Toughness.
docs/combat_design.md:167:Ogni Adult ha 1-2 trigger di Form Identity, dichiarati sul kit. Sono tracking flag round-scoped, non risorse visibili al player.
docs/combat_design.md:173:| Greymon | `OnFirstHitVsTagThisRound(Fire)` | `GrantEnergy(5)` |
docs/combat_design.md:174:| Garurumon | `OnFirstHitVsTagThisRound(Ice)` | `GrantEnergy(5)` |
docs/combat_design.md:175:| Kabuterimon | `OnFirstHitVsTagThisRound(Electric)` | `GrantEnergy(5)` |
docs/combat_design.md:176:| Kyubimon | `OnStatusApplied(Freeze)` | `SelfAdvance(15%)` |
docs/combat_design.md:177:| DORUgamon | `OnFirstSkillCastWithTag(Dark)` | Skill separata `dorugamon_form_identity` → `ToughnessHit(10)` |
docs/combat_design.md:178:| Angemon | `OnAttackVsAttribute(Virus)` | Skill separata `angemon_form_identity` → `Damage(15, Light)` |
docs/combat_design.md:180:**Pattern implementativo scelto (D050):** DORUgamon e Angemon usano un follow-up skill separato anziché i variant `BonusToughnessDamage`/`BonusDamageVsAttribute` dell'enum `Effect`. Quei variant sono stati rimossi in S09 come MVP debt — il `fire-a-separate-skill` approach è più semplice e garantisce lo stesso risultato comportamentale (verificato dai test `form_identity.rs` e dalle fixture TTK).
docs/combat_design.md:210:* **Break** (DORUmon line): forte contro elite/boss windows. *Debole contro*: Break Seal, Toughness adattiva.
docs/combat_design.md:226:* **Greymon** (Toughness Pressure vs Burning):
docs/combat_design.md:228:  * **Skill 1 — Mega Flame** (1 SP): Fire dmg. If Burning, +15% Toughness dmg.
docs/combat_design.md:229:  * **Skill 2 — Horn Impulse** (2 SP): Physical charge. High Toughness dmg.
docs/combat_design.md:230:  * **Ultimate — Tail Crash** (100 E): AoE Physical sweep. Massive Toughness dmg contro nemici Burning (niente Detonation).
docs/combat_design.md:231:  * **Form Identity**: First hit vs Burning each round grants 5 Energy o +10% Toughness dmg ("Se brucia, lo rompo").
docs/combat_design.md:270:  * **Ultimate — Onibidama** (100 E): AoE Fire/Dark. Se usato su nemici Slowed, triggera un Delay immediato su tutti i bersagli colpiti.
docs/combat_design.md:274:* **DORUmon** (Toughness Damage):
docs/combat_design.md:275:  * **Basic**: Physical hit. Contro un nemico ad alta Toughness (>50%), infligge Toughness damage bonus.
docs/combat_design.md:276:  * **Skill 1 — Metal Cannon** (1 SP): Physical dmg. High Toughness dmg.
docs/combat_design.md:277:  * **Skill 2 — Dash Metal** (1 SP): Physical hit. Bonus Toughness dmg se Toughness >50%.
docs/combat_design.md:278:  * **Ultimate — Metal Cannon** (100 E): AoE Toughness reduction.
docs/combat_design.md:279:  * **Passive**: +20% Toughness dmg vs target sopra 50% Toughness.
docs/combat_design.md:281:  * **Basic**: Physical hit. Bonus Toughness dmg se >50%. Se il nemico ha Shield (Break Seal), questo attacco intacca leggermente lo scudo.
docs/combat_design.md:282:  * **Skill 1 — Power Metal** (1 SP): Physical dmg. Applies Cracked se target >75% Toughness.
docs/combat_design.md:284:  * **Ultimate — Power Metal** (100 E): Heavy Physical. Se Cracked, prossimo direct hit guadagna +50% Toughness dmg.
docs/combat_design.md:285:  * **Form Identity**: Infligge Toughness dmg aumentato a target Cracked.
docs/combat_design.md:343:- **DORUmon Passive**: design prevede "+20% Toughness dmg vs target >50% Toughness" — non presente.
docs/combat_design.md:374:* **Mechanic**: Il bersaglio subisce il 50% in meno di HP damage dalle Secondary Actions (Follow-up, Counter, Detonation). Il Toughness damage rimane normale.
docs/combat_design.md:375:* **Counter**: Affidarsi a burst Primary, o usare Toughness pressure (DORUmon line) per scalfire il nemico invece di cercare DPS reaction-based.
docs/combat_design.md:379:* **Counter**: Il Toughness damage inflitto allo scudo riduce l'efficacia del prossimo Charged Attack del boss. DORUgamon e DORUmon restano utili per mitigarne i danni.
docs/combat_design.md:414:    triggers: Vec<ChipTrigger>, // quando il chip si attiva
docs/combat_design.md:500:  * **QTE (Precision Strike)**: Colpisci il punto debole per ignorare la Toughness.
docs/combat_design.md:549:* **Meccanica**: 'Armored' estremo. Riduce del 90% ogni danno non-critico e ha Toughness infinita.
docs/combat_design.md:581:* **Toughness varianti ridotte.**
docs/combat_design.md:594:  * *Modifica*: 3 finestre → 1 (End-of-Action). Start Window e Danger Window esplicite differite. Danger Window è gestita implicitamente dal trigger di Charged Attack + Emergency Guard.
